description:
A software development company is looking for a reliable Germany based Java Developer to be a part of a diverse international team.




The company is working on a cloud-based real estate management platform to revolutionize private property management, digitize it and adapt it to the needs of today's generation of landlords. The goal is to digitally map the entire lifecycle of a property and to use digital solutions to greatly simplify the administrative tasks of private landlords.




Tasks:




 * Collaborate with your team to design, develop and deliver product features;
 * Actively shape engineering culture;
 * Understanding and solving customer’s problems.




Requirements:




 * 3+ years of Java and Spring Boot;
 * Kotlin is a plus;
 * Basic understanding of agile software development (e.g.Scrum);
 * Good knowledge in software development (methods, databases, frameworks, tools and patterns);
 * Understand the values of Clean Code as well as continuous Integration and Test Driven Development;
 * Fluent spoken and written English.




Benefits: 




 * Flexibility: Up to 100% home office for more freedom; 
 * Remote work. It`s possible to work remotely being in Germany (not outside the country). Work outside of Germany - up to 20 days a year;
 * Teamwork: Regular team events & hackathons; 
 * Development: Continuously educate yourself with our learning budget;
 * Sport: Use our Gympass membership to stay healthy and mobile;
 * Mobility: Stay mobile at all times with a JobRad leasing;
 * Equipment: One-time 500€ bonus for your home office;
 * Paid vacations: 28 days per year.
